1. set up postgres database using following sequence, or edit itemsnonts.py connection to fit existing postgres server

docker run -d --name pg2 -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=password -e POSTGRES_DB=itemsnonts -v itemsnonts:/var/lib/postgresql/data postgres
    -change password as desired in above command; run it

2. edit host and password in tnoTables.py; runit to create tables in db
 
3. edit host and password in tnoAddItem.py; add some items to database

4. python3 itemsnonts.py

